<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910531-0144</DOCNO><DOCID>910531-0144.</DOCID><HL>   McDonnell Douglas   Gets F-15 Contract</HL><DATE>05/31/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A14</SO><CO>   MD GD OLN JCI WX ATK</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><LP>   WASHINGTON -- McDonnell Douglas Corp. was awarded a $110.9million Air Force contract for five F-15 aircraft for Israel.                                                                                                       </LP><TEXT>   General Dynamics Corp. was given $44.9 million incontracts for Army M-1 tanks and Navy nuclearballistic-missile submarine operations.                                                                                                          Planning Research Corp. won a $34 million Air Forcecontract for overseas navigation facilities.                                                                                                          Olin Corp. was awarded a $32.9 million Army contract for120-millimeter ammunition.                                                                                                          Johnson Controls World Services Inc., a unit of JohnsonControls Inc., got a $30.7 million Navy contract for supportof the Kings Bay, Ga., submarine base.                                                                                                          Westinghouse Electric Corp. was issued a $27.6 million AirForce contract for F-16 aircraft radars.                                                                                                          Alliant Techsystems Inc. won a $10.8 million Army contractfor fire-control system software.</TEXT></DOC>